  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(28) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "And though they found no cause of death in him.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Technically, the Sanhedrin had condemned our Lord on the charge of blasphemy (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 26:66",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), but they had been unable to prove the charge by any adequate evidence (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 26:60",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and finally condemned him by extorting words from His own lips. When they came before Pilate they shrank at first from urging that accusation, and contented themselves with stating in general terms that they had condemned Him as a malefactor (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 18:30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); though afterwards, as if seeking to terrify the wavering governor, they added that by their law He ought to die because He made Himself the Son of God (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 19:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and that by making Himself a king He spake against the emperor (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 19:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
